I agree with everything you said, including your observation that I'm
pushing the problem into user objects and the similar name lookup
problems that entails.  What I'm trying to do is come up with a good
model for how mail should be addressed and how those addresses (whatever
they are or look like) should be resolved and then figure out how to
implement it.  My interpretion of today's situation is implementation
constraints around which the current mail methodology has evolved.

